<paragraph id="8BEFF31FFFCDF13D42986B53FD8DF9DA" blockId="4.[151,634,1591,1618]" box="[151,634,1591,1618]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">
<heading id="D0A74473FFCDF13D42986B53FD8DF9DA" bold="true" box="[151,634,1591,1618]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C50889CFFCDF13D42986B53FD8DF9DA" authority="Kieffer, 1921" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1921" box="[151,634,1591,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Sclerodermus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formicarius">
<emphasis id="B9242F0DFFCDF13D42986B53FD8DF9DA" bold="true" box="[151,634,1591,1618]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">
<emphasis id="B9242F0DFFCDF13D42986B53FE24F9DA" bold="true" box="[151,467,1591,1618]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Sclerodermus formicarius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC18EEEFFCDF13D43D56B53FD8DF9DA" author="Kieffer, J. J." box="[474,634,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" pagination="36 - 41" refId="ref11811" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1921) Proctotrypides hotes des fourmis en Argentine. Anales de la Sociedad Cientifica Argentina, 91, 36 - 41." type="journal article" year="1921">Kieffer, 1921</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEFF31FFFCDF13D42986B1CFE3DF975" blockId="4.[151,1437,1656,2042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">
<materialsCitation id="3B38F942FFCDF13D42986B1CFE31F975" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3747936302" collectorName="Museo de la Plata" location="Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" specimenCount="1">
The 
<typeStatus id="54EB4DBDFFCDF13D42C46B1DFF0CF918" box="[203,251,1657,1683]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">type</typeStatus>
series of this species is lost. It was deposited in the private Bruch collection, which was supposed to be incorporated in the 
<location id="8E8FA5C4FFCDF13D437F6BF9FCDCF93D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03F94209FFCDF13C42986B53FCD2FF5E:8E8FA5C4FFCDF13D437F6BF9FCDCF93D" box="[368,811,1692,1719]" name="Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales</location>
“Bernardino Rivadavia” and 
<collectorName id="26A596C9FFCDF13D46796BF9FACBF93D" box="[1142,1340,1692,1719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">Museo de la Plata</collectorName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC18EEEFFCDF13D47466BF8FE96F950" author="Lanteri, A. A. &amp; Martinez, A." pageId="4" pageNumber="505" pagination="179 - 185" refId="ref12003" refString="Lanteri, A. A. &amp; Martinez, A. (2012) Carlos Bruch: pionero de los estudios entomologicos en la Argentina. Revista de la Sociedad de Entomologia de Argentina, 71 (3 - 4), 179 - 185." type="journal article" year="2012">Lanteri &amp; Martínez 2012</bibRefCitation>
). However, the first author was not able to find any material in his visit to the former, and the curator of the latter neither
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34AA094FFCDF13C42C86A6CFCD2FF5E" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="506" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEFF31FFFCDF13D42C86A6CFEEDF871" blockId="4.[151,1437,1656,2042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505">
The original description of this species by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC18EEEFFCDF13D40AC6A6CFCB2F8A8" author="Kieffer, J. J." box="[675,837,1800,1827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" pagination="36 - 41" refId="ref11811" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1921) Proctotrypides hotes des fourmis en Argentine. Anales de la Sociedad Cientifica Argentina, 91, 36 - 41." type="journal article" year="1921">Kieffer (1921)</bibRefCitation>
was mostly based on colouration and did not provide enough reliable taxonomic information to get a precise identification. The main characters that are possible to extract from the original description are: head quadrate, slightly longer than wide, and wider than thorax; eye subcircular, very close to mandible, and length less than 0.5 × distance to vertex crest; dorsal pronotal area long, metapectal-propodeal disc longer than mesoscutellum; wings absent; metasoma slightly longer than the rest of body, and as wide as head. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC18EEEFFCDF13D43CB6AD9FDAEF85C" author="Evans, H. E." box="[452,601,1980,2007]" pageId="4" pageNumber="505" pagination="103 - 106" refId="ref11161" refString="Evans, H. E. (1968) The genus Scleroderma in South America (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 22, 103 - 106." type="journal article" year="1968">Evans (1968)</bibRefCitation>
tentatively identified five Brazilian specimens. Nevertheless, this act lacks confidence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEFF31FFFCCF13C42C86DF3FCD2FF5E" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Given the scenario aforementioned, we have not keyed this species in order to avoid any future unprecise identification, since it is unidentifiable in the present time.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
